The Federal Government on Friday declared Boko Haram members detained at the Medium Security Custodial Centre, Kuje, Abuja, who escaped during the ISWAP attack last Tuesday, wanted.
the Nigerian Correctional Service (NCoS) in a statement on Friday, published the names and pictures of 69 inmates who escaped from the correctional facility during the Tuesday   attack by ISWAP.
The statement reads: “The following are faces and names of Inmates with Boko Haram/ terrorism cases who escaped from Kuje Correctional Centre during the jail attack on 5th July 2022,” it said.
“If you see any of these people or have useful information which may lead to their recapture, please Call 07000099999, 09060004598 or 08075050006 or any law enforcement agency nearest to you. We guarantee to keep your information anonymous.”
